               <msContents>
                  <summary>This volume entitled <title>Sukhanān-i Anṣarī</title> (Speeches of
                     Anṣārī) contains mainly lines of poetry culled from various works by ʻAbd Allāh
                     ibn Muḥammad Anṣārī Haravī (1006–1089). Unfortunately incomplete, unsigned, and
                     undated, secondary inscriptions attribute this volume to famed calligrapher Mīr
                     ‘Alī Tabrīzī (fl. 1340–1420), but this appears false, as it was probably
                     completed in the sixteenth century then restored in the seventeenth or
                     eighteenth century.</summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_844-item1">
                     <author key="person_19703891" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/19703891/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Anṣārī al-Harawī, ʻAbd
                           Allāh ibn Muḥammad, 1006-1089</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Hirawī, Khawājah Abdullāh
                           Anṣarī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Pīr-i Anṣār</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">أنصاري الهروي، عبد الله بن محمد</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">خواجه عبدالله انصارى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="dub" key="person_18623774">Mīr ‘Alī Tabrīzī, fl.
                        1340–1420</editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7189">Sukhanān-i Anṣarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_7189">Sukhanān-i Pīr-i
                        Harāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7189">سخنان انصاري</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_7189">سخنان پیر هرات</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> الحمد لله رب العالمین و الصلوة و السلم علی محند و آله
                        اجمعین. این سخنانیست که حصرت قطب الاوتاد الشیخ الکبیر الاستاد خواجه عبدالله
                        انصاری قدس الله سره در هر بانی فرموده‌اند تا هرکس از هر سحن در خور... </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"> یا رب! دل پاک و جان آگاهم ده * آه شب و گریهٔ سحرگاهم
                        ده | در راه خود اول ز خودم بی‌خود کن * بی‌خود چو شدم ز خود به خود راهم ده. </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>In his catalogue, former owner Duncan Forbes spuriously attributes this
                        volume to famed calligrapher Mīr ‘Alī Tabrīzī, probably on the basis of
                        secondary inscriptions in the volume, but this appears false.</note>
                  </msItem>
